    AbstractAmpAutoCompleteTextField

    public abstract class AbstractAutoCompleteTextField<CHOICE>
extends org.apache.wicket.markup.html.form.TextField
    Auto-Complete text field that allows capture of choice selections (rather than just strings). Replacement for AutoCompleteTextField.
    See Also:
    https://cwiki.apache.org/WICKET/autocomplete-using-a-wicket-model.html, Serialized Form

        public final java.util.Iterator<CHOICE> getChoices(java.lang.String searchTextInput)
        Call-back method that should return an iterator over all possible assist choice objects. These objects will be passed to the renderer to generate output. Usually it is enough to return an iterator over strings.
        Parameters:
        searchTextInput - current input
        Returns:
        iterator over all possible choice objects

      • findChoice

        public final CHOICE findChoice()
        Finds the selection by cycling through the current choices and matching the choices value. If the selected choice is found the choices will be reset and the choice will be returned.

        NOTE: Assumes that the selection choice values are unique

        Returns:
        the found selection model by name (null if it cannot be found)
